This project uses a simple AWS architecture:

- One EC2 instance running Apache, PHP, and WordPress
- One RDS database storing WordPress data
- AWS Backup for EC2 snapshots stored in S3
- CloudWatch Monitoring enabled from the EC2 console (no manual agent installation)
- IAM roles:
  - SSM role for remote access
  - CloudWatch Agent role for metrics
- One AMI image used as a backup template
